I built an XPath expression to extract the contents of an XML element. I tested this XPath in a utility I created that executes the expression, and writes the results to the file system. The XPath expression worked perfectly, and returned the contents of the XML element. Here&rsquo;s a quick and dirty example &hellip;
My XML file:
&lt;ns0:Example xmlns:ns0=&quot;[http://example/](http://example/)&quot;&gt; &lt;ns0:Contents&gt;1169861&lt;/ns0:Contents&gt; &lt;/ns0:Example&gt;  And my XPath expression:
/*[local-name()='Example' and namespace-uri()='http://example/']/*[local-name()='Contents' and namespace-uri()='http://example/']/text()  (Don&rsquo;t forget the &ldquo;/text()&rdquo; at the end, or you&rsquo;ll get the entire element!
